Item received within 3daya after orderingOrdered Nano collagen and royal jelly N times,Detox & Cleanse is the first time, inquiry from 18th April till received parcel still not replied !Ordered on the weekend and received on wednesday. Have not tried the item so can't comment on taste. Very disappointed with the price as the price now dropped lower than the initial launch price..feel abit cheated as I purchased 4 tins to support seller as I recently tried the collagen and royal jelly which was good. I thought seller would give a good discount during the initial launch to reward regular customers who try out their new product but never expected price would drop another $4 per tin on the day I received my order...I bought 4 tins, so total of $16 is quite a significant difference. :(

Edited to add:
To be fair to the seller, a free bag was included with my order (long champ look alike) so that probably explains the extra cost. Items are also always neatly packed and care was taken to include a scoop with each tin of shake. The tins are made of metal, and are quite small, but packed quite full. Love the compact size. If the nano collagen could be packed in similar tin would be great. 

Tried the shake, and taste wise it is like banana+orange...tastes like fruit juice so quite palatable. Slightly sweet so probably better if mixed in milk than just water.

Latest update:
The company called and apologised for the price difference. Apparently the prices are in part controlled by qoo10 and not always within their control. I applaud their excellent customer service. Its very rare to find a seller that actually cares what their customers think. Their explanation makes me feel better about supporting their company, and I will continue to do so as their products have been great so far. :) Hopefully they can give regular customers a heads up when there are gd deals, then we don't need to keep monitoring the price.

I had another scoop of the detox with just 200ml water (earlier I mixed in a multi grain shake powder) and it did taste just like tropical fruit juice. I still find it on the sweet side for me, so would use 300-400ml water in future. Its not very thick despite the fiber, so don't expect it to be like a smoothie. If you want it thicker can try adding 1tbsp chia seeds and/or 1tbsp psyllum husks and let it sit for awhile to thicken before drinking.
